# shadcn/ui Standards - STRICT ENFORCEMENT

This project uses **shadcn/ui EXCLUSIVELY** for ALL UI components. **ABSOLUTELY NO CUSTOM UI COMPONENTS ARE ALLOWED**.

## üö´ ZERO TOLERANCE POLICY

**RULE**: Every UI element MUST use a shadcn/ui component. If a shadcn/ui component exists for your use case, you MUST use it. If it doesn't exist, install it first.

**NO EXCEPTIONS**: 
- No custom buttons, cards, inputs, modals, dialogs, or any UI elements
- No custom Tailwind CSS classes for layout or styling without shadcn/ui
- No HTML elements styled with custom classes (button, div, span, etc.)
- No custom form components

## Setup Commands

### Initialize shadcn/ui (if not already set up)
```bash
npx shadcn@latest init
```

### Essential Components - Install These First
```bash
npx shadcn@latest add button
npx shadcn@latest add card
npx shadcn@latest add input
npx shadcn@latest add dialog
npx shadcn@latest add form
npx shadcn@latest add label
npx shadcn@latest add textarea
npx shadcn@latest add select
npx shadcn@latest add badge
npx shadcn@latest add alert
```

### Install ANY component you need
```bash
npx shadcn@latest add [component-name]
```

## MANDATORY Usage Rules

1. **BEFORE** creating any UI element, check shadcn/ui documentation
2. **INSTALL** the required shadcn/ui component if not already added
3. **USE ONLY** shadcn/ui components - never create custom alternatives
4. **COMPOSITION**: Combine multiple shadcn/ui components instead of creating custom ones

## Clerk Authentication - MUST USE shadcn/ui

**Clerk sign-in/sign-up buttons MUST use shadcn/ui Button component with modal triggers:**

```tsx
// ‚úÖ REQUIRED - Clerk with shadcn/ui Button and Dialog
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"
import { Dialog, DialogContent, DialogTrigger } from "@/components/ui/dialog"
import { SignIn, SignUp } from "@clerk/nextjs"

export function AuthButtons() {
  return (
    <>
      <Dialog>
        <DialogTrigger asChild>
          <Button variant="default">Sign In</Button>
        </DialogTrigger>
        <DialogContent className="sm:max-w-md">
          <SignIn />
        </DialogContent>
      </Dialog>

      <Dialog>
        <DialogTrigger asChild>
          <Button variant="outline">Sign Up</Button>
        </DialogTrigger>
        <DialogContent className="sm:max-w-md">
          <SignUp />
        </DialogContent>
      </Dialog>
    </>
  )
}

// ‚ùå FORBIDDEN - Custom button for Clerk
<button onClick={() => signIn()}>Sign In</button>
<div className="auth-button">Sign Up</div>
```

